title: How to Make a Gluten Free Fall Harvest Cake

steps.headline: Mix together sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon, baking soda, salt, nutmeg, ginger, oil, vanilla, and eggs.
steps.description: Add pumpkin to mixture and stir well.

steps.headline: Stir in 2 cups of sifted flour, ½ cup at a time.
Bake 60-70 minutes at 350 °F (177 °C) in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Ice with cream-cheese frosting, and sprinkle with nuts.

text: Mix together sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon, baking soda, salt, nutmeg, ginger, oil, vanilla, and eggs. Add pumpkin to mixture and stir well. Stir in 2 cups of sifted flour, ½ cup at a time. Stir in apples and pecans. Bake 60-70 minutes at 350 °F (177 °C) in a greased and floured Bundt pan.  Ice with cream-cheese frosting, and sprinkle with nuts.  Finished.
